<div class="row">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Badges</h1>
    <p>Badges are great for displaying counters, such as number of emails, likes for your social networks or even available servers on your monitoring tool.</p>

    <br />
    <div class="row">
      <div class="eight columns">
        <h4><em>Building the markup</em></h4>
        <p>The markup to create badges is fairly simple, short and handle through data attributes.</p>
        <%= code_block do
          %q{&lt;a href="#" class="badge" data-badge="25">Inbox&lt;/a>}
        end %>
    </div>
    <div class="four columns html no-padding border bottom top">
      <div class="container result">
        <span>RESULT</span>
        <div class="wrapper">
          <a href="#" class="badge" data-badge="25">Inbox</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
      <h4><em>Powerful mixin</em></h4>
      <p>We only provide one color for the badge but that doesn't mean you can't add all you want. A simple but powerful mixin was put together to achieve this.</p>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="six columns">
          <%= code_block "scss" do
            %q{.badge.primary {
    @include badge-background-variation($background-color: #3F51B5);
  }}
          end %>
      </div>
      <div class="six columns">
        <%= code_block do
          %q{&lt;a href="#" class="badge primary" data-badge="25">Inbox&lt;/a>}
        end %>
    </div>
      </div>

      <h4><em>Available arguments</em></h4>

      <table class="responsive striped shadow">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Argument Name</th>
            <th>Description</th>
            <th>Default value</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>$background-color</td>
            <td>Is the background color for the label to add.</td>
            <td><span class="label">Required argument</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>$font-weight</td>
            <td>The font weight for the badge.</td>
            <td><span class="label">600</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>$color</td>
            <td>The font color for the badge.</td>
            <td><span class="label">#FFF</span></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <h4><em>Available Sass Variables</em></h2>
      <p>You can customize the badge really easy by changing the our Sass variables.</p>
      <pre>
<code class="language-scss" data-language="scss">
  $badge-text-font-size: px-to-rems(16) !default;
  $badge-text-color: #B6B6B6 !default;
  $badge-background-color: #FF4081 !default;
  $badge-width: px-to-rems(22) !default;
  $badge-height: $badge-width !default;
  $badge-font-weight: 600 !default;
  $badge-font-size: 75% !default;
  $badge-color: #FFF !default;
  $badge-right-position: px-to-rems(-22) !default;
  $badge-top-position: px-to-rems(-11) !default;
  $badge-no-background-color: #212121 !default;
</code>
      </pre>

    </div>

  </div>
</div>



